10731).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="157" pageNumber="158" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="157" pageNumber="158">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="157" pageNumber="158">
Resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burm. f., Fl. Ind. (N. L. Burman) Prodr. Fl. Cap. 47. 1768. (Burman" authorityYear="1768" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus spinosus" order="Solanales" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">Convolvulus spinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but most easily distinguished by the obovate leaves and all five sepals equal in size and shape.
</paragraph>
